READ SCENARIOS
1.  User Login 
    Lookup Key : Phone/Email
    API : POST /auth/login
    DB Query : findOne({phone: <>}) or findOne({email: <>})
    Read heavy 

2.  Fetch User Profile
    Lookup Key : _id
    API : GET /users/{userId}
    DB Query : findOne({_id: <>})
    Not Read heavy 

3.  Fetch User Details During Order Placement
    Lookup Key : _id
    API : GET /users/{userId}
    DB Query : findOne({_id: <>})
    Not Read heavy 

4.  Admin vieweing users
    Lookup Key : status and role
    API : GET /users?status=active
    DB Query : find({ status: "active" })
    Not Read heavy 


WRITE SCENARIOS
1.  User Signup (Create new user)
    API : POST /users
    DB Query : insertOne({})
    Write heavy 

2.  Update User Details
    API : PUT /users/{userId}
    DB Query : updateOne({_id: <>}, {$set: {}})
    Not Write heavy

3.  Delete user
    API : DELETE /users/{userId}
    DB Query : deleteOne({_id: <>})
    Not Write heavy

4.  Update Status (Active / Blocked)
    Admin changes user status by phone number
    API : PUT /users/{userId}/status
    DB Query : updateOne({phone: <>}, {$set: {status: <>}})
    Not Write heavy

5.  Update Role (Admin / User)
    Admin changes user role by phone number
    API : PUT /users/{userId}/role
    DB Query : updateOne({phone: <>}, {$set: {role: <>}})
    Not Write heavy


INDEX 
db.users.createIndex({ email: 1 }) // Needed for login,updates
db.users.createIndex({ phone: 1 }) // Neeed for login,updates
db.users.createIndex({ role: 1 }) // Needed for admin dashboard so that we can filter users by role
db.users.createIndex({ status: 1 }) // Needed for admin dashboard so that we can filter users by status